---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { type Lang } from '../../data/i18n';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [{ params: { lang: 'en' } }, { params: { lang: 'es' } }];
}

const { lang } = Astro.params as { lang: Lang };
---

<BaseLayout lang={lang} title="Personal Roadmap" description="Luis Tapia's personal roadmap and learning journey.">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Personal Roadmap</h1>
    <p>This is a private roadmap to track my core interests and learning journey.</p>

    <section class="roadmap-section">
      <h2>1. Compiler Construction</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Explore advanced parsing techniques.</li>
        <li>Deepen understanding of semantic analysis and code generation.</li>
        <li>Continue contributing to or exploring frameworks like CBS (PLanCompS).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="roadmap-section">
      <h2>2. Higher Education &amp; Pedagogy</h2>
      <p>Building on my <strong>Diplomado in Higher Education</strong>, I'm focusing on:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Integrating software engineering principles into educational curricula.</li>
        <li>Exploring active learning methodologies for technical subjects.</li>
        <li>Developing effective mentoring strategies for junior developers and students.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="roadmap-section">
      <h2>3. Medical &amp; Informatics Integration</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Investigate the intersection of software engineering and healthcare.</li>
        <li>Explore data interoperability standards (like FHIR).</li>
        <li>Understand the challenges of building reliable and compliant medical software.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="roadmap-section">
      <h2>4. Context Assembly for AI Agents</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Study how large language models utilize context and memory.</li>
        <li>Experiment with building custom agents and optimizing their prompt context window.</li>
        <li>Explore vector databases and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) techniques.</li>
        <li>Investigate agentic workflows and autonomous agent architectures.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section class="roadmap-section">
      <h2>Upcoming Content (Possible Posts)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><em>"Reflections on Higher Education: Applying the Diplomado to CS"</em></li>
        <li><em>"The Logic of Teaching: How Compilers Taught Me to Teach"</em></li>
        <li><em>"Medical Software: Beyond CRUD Applications"</em></li>
        <li><em>"Building a Better Context: RAG Strategies for AI Agents"</em></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p class="status"><em>Status: Work in progress. Updated periodically.</em></p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }
  .roadmap-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .roadmap-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .status {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
